You are building Pristine Pond Solutions, a premium React website for a Louisiana
pond and lake management company. Stack: React 19, Vite 6, Tailwind v4 (native @theme),
React Router v7, Framer Motion, Lucide icons. Components are .jsx (not TypeScript).

Brand:
- Navy        #1B2A4A   primary surface, headlines on light bg
- Gold        #D4A843   single accent, used sparingly (CTAs, eyebrows, hairlines)
- Lake Blue   #2E7D9C   secondary, water/links
- Moss Green  #4A7C59   tertiary, nature/eco signals
- Sand        #F5F0E8   warm off-white background
- Slate       #334155   body text
Tint all neutrals warm. Never use pure #000 or #fff.

Typography:
- Outfit (display, headlines, eyebrows)
- Inter (body, UI)
- Playfair Display italic (pull quotes only)

Design rules:
- Mobile-first. Touch targets >= 44px.
- Animations: Framer Motion with ease-out exponential curves. No bounce.
- Never animate layout properties (width/height). Use transform + opacity.
- No gradient text. No glassmorphism by default. No identical card grids.
- No em dashes in copy. Use commas, colons, semicolons, parentheses.
- Cards are not the default; use them only when they're the best affordance.
- Vary spacing for rhythm; don't reach for the same padding everywhere.
- All interactive elements need accessible focus states (focus-visible:ring).

Path alias: `@/` resolves to `./src/`.

Source of truth: src/data/site.js for company info, src/data/services.js for the
service catalog. Components pull from these; don't hardcode copy in components.
